Zach's Bootcamp
===============
The most common ownership model
Primary software engineer - logging/exports
Primary Data Engineer - Pipeline, Master Data 
Primary Data Analyst/scientist - Metrics/Dashboarfs, Experiments.

What happens when these crossed boundaries persist?
Burnout
Bad team dynamic
The blame game
Bad cross-functional support

Centralized vs Embedded Teams
Centralized : many Data Engineers in one team, knowledge sharing DE's supporting DE's, Prioritization can get complex.
Embedded : Data Engineers in other ebgineering teams, DE gains deep domain knowledge, Islands of responsibility DE's can feel isolated.




Common issues in the pipelines you're bound to face as a Data Engineer
-Skewed pipelines that OOM.
-Missing Data / schema change of the upstream data.
-Backfill needs to trigger downstream data sets.
-Business questions about where and how to use data.

Fix Skew
-Best Option
  Upgrade to spark3 and enable adaptive query execution.
  Bump up the executor memory and hope it's not more skewed later.
  Update the job to include a skew join salt.

Missing data / Schema Change
Pre check your upstream data!
  This will prevent your pipeline from running if its missing data!
Track down the upstream qwner
  Fill out a task/ticket/etc to have them fix the issue (Both unlock and long-term fix)

Backfill triggers downstream pipelines
Small migrations
  Do a paralel backfill into table_backfill
  if everythin looks good, do the "shell game"
    -Rename production to production_old
    -Rename table_bakcfill to production
If people need a lot more time migrate (a lot more painful)
  -Build a parallel pipeline that populates table_v2 while prodution gets migrated
  -After all references to production have been updates, drop prodution and rename table_v2(and all its references) to production.

Business questions
-Set an SLA on when you'll get back to people. Maybe its 2hours maybe it's a day?
-Consolidate common questions into a document so you dont have to keep amswering the same questions over and over again.
-Is this the same or different oncall from the pipeline oncall?
-Make sure your analytics partners are looped in there!

Path forward for painful pipelines
-The only thing better than optimized is deprecated!
-Is there anything that can be done?
  New technology
  Better data modeling
  Bucketing?
  Sampling?
-Depricated without a replacement can eb hard sell!














